 Encores can be stopped by reforming them in the past. The Legends test this idea when serial killer Freddy Meyers is encored in 2004 and attacks his high school reunion. Sara, Ava, and Mick head there to stop him while Ray, Nate, and Behrad take [[Nora Darhk]] to 1989 to become Freddy's fairy godmother and fix his prom night. The Legends find evidence of a prank that Freddy's date, Tiffany, and a jock were going to pull, but the former has a change of heart and gets the latter to confess. With Nora's encouragement, Freddy uses his last wish to perform a dance number to show his \"true self\". Zari has flashes of her other life and escapes the ''Waverider'' just as the real killer attacks the prom. To Freddy's horror, the killer is his overly-possessive mother Kathy, whose crime he took the fall for. Behrad manages to knock her out, undoing her damage in 2004. The Legends reconvene at the reunion, learning Freddy and Tiffany got married while Mick reconnects with an old girlfriend, Ali. Meanwhile, Constantine resorts to desperate measures to stop Astra's Encores by facing her mother's ghost, much to Charlie and Gary's dismay.\n |LineColor       = CF905C\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Legends of Tomorrow (season 5)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 72\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n |Title           = A Head of Her Time\n |DirectedBy      = Avi Youabian\n |WrittenBy       = Morgan Faust\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|18}}\n |ProdCode        = T13.21904\n |Viewers         = 0.72<ref name=\"5.04\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-2-18-2020.html |title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 2.18.2020 |last=Metcalf |first=Mitch |date=February 20, 2020 |website=Showbuzz Daily |access-date=February 20, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Sara leaves Ava in charge of the Legends while she heads to Star City for business. An Encore pops up in 1793 France, causing a massacre. The Legends investigate, finding [[Marie Antoinette]], who was encored after her execution. Discovering Marie has magic perfume, the Legends capture her, separating her head from her body. Not understanding how dangerous the perfume is, Zari steals it when Behrad takes her back to 2040 for her own perfume's launch. Behrad, Nate, and Ava go to stop her while Marie's body gets free and steals Mick's Heat Gun. Zari is pushed into a fountain to wash off the perfume and escorted back to the ''Waverider'' before she can damage history any further. They return just as Mick and Ray pin down Marie's body and lock it in [[Martin Stein (Arrowverse)|Martin Stein]]'s old lab, but Astra recalls her back to Hell. Meanwhile, Constantine is tormented by a ghost that was part of his Earth-Prime counterpart's Newcastle crew when she was alive. She reveals that the Loom of Fate is the key and Charlie knows where it is. Charlie reveals she destroyed it, just as Constantine starts coughing up blood.\n|LineColor       = CF905C\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Legends of Tomorrow (season 5)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 73\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n |Title           = Mortal Khanbat\n |DirectedBy      = [[Caity Lotz]]\n |WrittenBy       = Grainne Godfree & Mark Bruner\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|25}}\n |ProdCode        = T13.21905\n |Viewers         = 0.74<ref name=\"5.05\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-2-25-2020.html |title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 2.25.2020 |last=Metcalf |first=Mitch |date=February 26, 2020 |website=Showbuzz Daily |access-date=February 26, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = When he is diagnosed with stage 4 lung cancer, Constantine concludes Astra tampered with his soul coin and forces Ray and Gary to help him find a way to extend his life, but to no avail. Poisoning himself, Constantine goes to Hell and tells Astra that he promised her mother that he would use the Loom of Fate to save them, so she gives him his remaining years back. Meanwhile, the Legends head to 1990s Hong Kong, where [[Genghis Khan]] is attempting to start a new empire by using a hell sword and the contemporary Triads to force [[Charles, Prince of Wales|Prince Charles]] to hand over control of the city to him. Using her powers to disguise herself as Prince Charles, Charlie manages to steal Khan's sword and kill him with it. Following this, Charlie reveals to her friends that she is actually [[Clotho]] of the [[Moirai|Fates]] and that she scattered the Loom of Fate across the multiverse to give everyone free will. Due to the Crisis however, the pieces are now on Earth-Prime and her sisters are out for revenge against her.\n |LineColor       = CF905C\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Legends of Tomorrow (season 5)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 74\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n |Title           = Mr. Parker's Cul-De-Sac\n |DirectedBy      = Ben Hernandez Bray\n |WrittenBy       = Keto Shimizu & James Eagan\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|10}}\n |ProdCode        = T13.21906\n |Viewers         = 0.73<ref name=\"5.06\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-10-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 3.10.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=March 11, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Ray plans a romantic dinner for Nora at Constantine's place, planning to propose to her while Nate and Behrad babysit her latest charge, Pippa, on the ''Waverider''. Unfortunately, her father [[Damien Darhk (Arrowverse)|Damien Darhk]] is \"encored\" following [[Mallus (Legends of Tomorrow)|Mallus]]' demise and steals past Gary's time courier to get to 2020. When Constantine blunders in, Nora tries to pass him off as her lover and her friends as her minions. The ruse fails, forcing Nora to reveal the truth, disappointing Damien. After Pippa wishes everyone into the TV show, ''Mr Parker's Cul-De-Sac'', Nora tells Damien that being a fairy godmother helps her with the trauma of being raised by Mallus' cult instead of him. Damien gives his blessing and everyone is released. Ray and Nora have a makeshift wedding, with Damien advising his new son-in-law that Nora cannot live her life to the fullest as a Legend. He discreetly leaves and kills himself with Khan's blade. Meanwhile, Mick learns someone has libeled his books. With Zari's help, he tracks down a girl named Lita, whom he learns is his and Ali's daughter. Not wishing to taint Lita's life with his presence, Mick erases the visit from everyone's minds.\n |LineColor       = CF905C\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Legends of Tomorrow (season 5)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 75\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 7\n |Title           = Romeo v Juliet: Dawn of Justness\n |DirectedBy      = Alexandra La Roche\n |WrittenBy       = Ray Utarnachitt & Matthew Maala\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|17}}\n |ProdCode        = T13.21907\n |Viewers         = 0.67<ref name=\"5.07\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-17-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 3.17.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=March 18, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = While in 16th century England to retrieve the first piece of the Loom of Fate, the Legends inadvertently inspire [[William Shakespeare]] to rewrite ''[[Romeo and Juliet]]'' as a superhero story just as he was about to write its ending. Even worse, they fail to wipe his mind correctly following a bar fight. Initially, they decide to let the playwright be as they got what they came for. However, Sara refuses to accept this and forces her team to return and convince Shakespeare to write ''Romeo and Juliet'' as intended. After his boss withdraws his actors before a performance, Shakespeare becomes despondent until the Legends offer to fill in for them. Following this, Ray and Nora leave the Legends to live their lives together. Meanwhile, Astra attains a special viewing device to spy on Constantine. However, he catches on quickly and uses a spell to knock her out. When she comes to, she realizes what Constantine is really searching for.\n |LineColor       = CF905C\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Legends of Tomorrow (season 5)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 76\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 8\n |Title           = Zari, Not Zari\n |RTitle          = <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/listings/20200409cw07/|title=(#509) \"Zari, Not Zari\"|website=The Futon Critic |access-date=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n |DirectedBy      = Kevin Mock\n |WrittenBy       = Morgan Faust & Tyron Carter\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|21}}\n |ProdCode        = T13.21909<ref>{{Cite tweet |number=1187442474815328256 |user=ketomizu |title=#LegendsOfTomorrow episode 509 is now in production! Written by @morganfaust and @tyronsaidso and directed by @kevmock |author-link=Keto Shimizu |date=October 24, 2019 |last=Shimizu |first=Keto}}</ref>\n |Viewers         =\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = CF905C\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Legends of Tomorrow (season 5)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 77\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 9\n |Title           = The Great British Fake Off\n |RTitle          = <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/listings/20200312cw06/|title=(#510) \"The Great British Fake Off\"|website=The Futon Critic |access-date=March 12, 2020}}</ref>\n |DirectedBy      = David Geddes\n |WrittenBy       = Jackie Canino\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|28}}<ref>http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/dcs-legends-of-tomorrow/listings/</ref>\n |ProdCode        = T13.21910<ref>{{Cite tweet |number=1192262676463751168 |user=ketomizu |title=#LegendsOfTomorrow episode 510 is now in production! Written by our script coordinator 