gends-of-tomorrow-mister-parkers-cul-de-sac-preview/</ref>\n* Erik Gow as Mr. Parker\n* [[Mina Sundwall]] as Lita\n* [[Rowan Schlosberg]] as [[William Shakespeare]]\n}}\n\n== Production ==\n=== Development ===\nOn January 31, 2019, [[The CW]] renewed the series for a fifth season.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/cw-renews-flash-charmed-riverdale-supernatural-6-more-1181714 |title=CW Renews 'The Flash,' 'Charmed,' 'Riverdale,' 'Supernatural,' 6 More |last=Goldberg |first=Lesley |date=January 31, 2019 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190202015411/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/cw-renews-flash-charmed-riverdale-supernatural-6-more-1181714 |archive-date=February 2, 2019 |access-date=May 17, 2019}}</ref> [[Phil Klemmer]] and [[Keto Shimizu]] serve as the season's [[showrunner]]s.<ref name=\"Ashe\" />\n\n=== Writing ===\nThe fourth season ended with [[Astra Logue (Arrowverse)|Astra Logue]] restoring many notorious historical figures like [[Genghis Khan]], [[Joseph Stalin]] and [[Charles Manson]] to life. Klemmer said these characters would be called \"Encores\" and have the [[villain of the week]] treatment, while the [[Big Bad]] of the season would not be demon-related,<ref name=\"Ashe\" /> later revealed by both Shimizu and Klemmer to be Astra.<ref name=\"SwannEW\" /> He explained this was done with the intention of returning to the series' roots, of being rooted \"more firmly in history and historical periods and figures and true villains\". Klemmer added that the season would explore what [[Zari Tomaz]] would look like if she \"lived a more charmed life\" and did not come from a \"dystopian, authoritarian future\".<ref name=\"new Zari\" /> The season also explores Zari's relationship with her brother [[Behrad Tarazi]].<ref name=\"EW\" /> Following the season four finale, the Time Bureau was shut down and its former director [[Ava Sharpe]] was left unemployed. The fifth season sees Ava living on the ''Waverider'' with her girlfriend [[Sara Lance]], trying to figure out how she fits on the team. It will continue to grow the \"Avalance\" relationship, and also feature Sara developing a superpower.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://ew.com/comic-con/2019/07/17/legends-of-tomorrow-star-caity-lotz-reveals-sara-gets-a-superpower-in-season-5/ |title=DC's Legends of Tomorrow star Caity Lotz reveals Sara gets a superpower in season 5 |last=Agard |first=Chancellor |date=July 17, 2019 |website=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190823080958/https://ew.com/comic-con/2019/07/17/legends-of-tomorrow-star-caity-lotz-reveals-sara-gets-a-superpower-in-season-5/ |archive-date=August 23, 2019 |access-date=August 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Casting ===\nMain cast members [[Brandon Routh]], [[Caity Lotz]], [[Maisie Richardson-Sellers]], [[Tala Ashe]], [[Jes Macallan]], [[Amy Pemberton|Amy Louise Pemberton]], [[Courtney Ford]], [[Nick Zano]], [[Dominic Purcell]] and [[Matt Ryan (actor)|Matt Ryan]] return as [[Ray Palmer (Arrowverse)|Ray Palmer]],<ref name=\"Day 1\" /> Sara Lance,<ref name=\"Lotz\" /> [[Charlie (Arrowverse)|Charlie]],<ref name=\"Sellers\" /> Zari Tomaz,<ref name=\"Ashe\" /> Ava Sharpe,<ref name=\"Macallan\" /> Gideon,<ref name=\"Pemberton\" /> [[Nora Darhk]],<ref name=\"Ford\" /> [[Nate Heywood (Arrowverse)|Nate Heywood]], [[Mick Rory (Arrowverse)|Mick Rory]],<ref name=\"Day 1\" /> and [[John Constantine (Arrowverse)|John Constantine]] respectively.<ref name=\"Ryan\" /> This is the final season for Routh and Ford as series regulars,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/08/brandon-routh-courtney-ford-exit-dcs-legends-of-tomorrow-series-regulars-season-5-the-cw-1202702311/ |title='DC's Legends Of Tomorrow': Brandon Routh & Courtney Ford To Depart the CW Drama As Series Regulars |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |date=August 22, 2019 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190823033935/https://deadline.com/2019/08/brandon-routh-courtney-ford-exit-dcs-legends-of-tomorrow-series-regulars-season-5-the-cw-1202702311/ |archive-date=August 23, 2019 |access-date=August 23, 2019}}</ref> with the episode \"Romeo v Juliet: Dawn of Justness\" marking their final appearance.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/legends-of-tomorrow-producers-on-why-and-how-these/1100-6473823/ |title=Legends Of Tomorrow Producers On Why And How These Main Characters Are Leaving |last=Hayner |first=Chris E. |date=February 27, 2020 |website=GameSpot |url-status=live |archive-url=http://archive.today/nzKRZ |archive-date=February 28, 2020 |access-date=February 28, 2020}}</ref> Olivia Swann, who guest starred as Astra Logue in the fourth season, was promoted to the main cast for the fifth season.<ref name=\"SwannEW\" /> [[Ramona Young]], who starred as [[Mona Wu]] in the fourth season, returned as a guest star.<ref name=\"Ramona\">{{Cite web |url=https://tv.avclub.com/allow-the-legends-of-tomorrow-to-re-introduce-themselve-1841146784 |title=Allow the Legends Of Tomorrow to re-introduce themselves in a raucous post-Crisis premiere |last=Shoemaker |first=Alison |date=January 21, 2020 |website=[[The A.V. Club]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200122102501/https://tv.avclub.com/allow-the-legends-of-tomorrow-to-re-introduce-themselve-1841146784 |archive-date=January 22, 2020 |access-date=January 22, 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\nFilming began on July 15, 2019.<ref name=\"Day 1\" /> The fifth episode of the season, \"Mortal Khanbat\", marks Lotz's directorial debut.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://tvline.com/2019/07/19/mayans-mc-season-2-trailer-video-fx/ |title=TVLine Items: Mayans M.C. Trailer, Legends' Caity Lotz Directs and More |last=Gelman |first=Vlada |date=July 19, 2019 |website=[[TVLine]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190720032332/https://tvline.com/2019/07/19/mayans-mc-season-2-trailer-video-fx/ |archive-date=July 20, 2019 |access-date=July 20, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Mortal Khanbat\">{{Cite tweet |number=1167099491779899397 |user=caitylotz |title=MORTAL KAHNBAT!!!!! \ud83d\udc4aToday is the first day of Production for the first episode of television I will direct. Can't even begin to express my gratitude to Phil and the Legends writers, Greg Berlanti, CW and Warner Brothers for this opportunity. Now let's go do this!!! |author-link=Caity Lotz |date=August 29, 2019 |last=Lotz |first=Caity}}</ref> Filming [[Wrap (filmmaking)|wrapped]] in January 2020.<ref>{{Cite tweet |number=1222814879590936578 |user=caitylotz |title=Tomorrow is the last day of filming for season 5 of  @TheCW_Legends  \ud83d\udc95\ud83d\ude4f\ud83c\udf89 |author=Caity Lotz |author-link=Caity Lotz |date=January 30, 2020}}</ref> Despite the \"[[Crisis on Infinite Earths (Arrowverse)|Crisis on Infinite Earths]]\" episode being the eighth episode filmed,<ref>{{Cite tweet |number=1187802374905065472 |user=ketomizu |title=508 airs before the rest of our season. But it was shot as our 8th episode, production-wise. |author=Keto Shimizu |author-link=Keto Shimizu |date=October 25, 2019 |access-date=November 27, 2019}}</ref> the events of the episode occur before the rest of the season.<ref>{{Cite tweet |number=1187848452249538560 |user=ketomizu |title=To further clarify: the events of 508 occur BEFORE 501. We had to write the sequel before the original, so to speak. |author=Keto Shimizu |author-link=Keto Shimizu |date=October 26, 2019 |access-date=November 27, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite tweet |number=1197908197102669824 |user=mguggenheim |title=Before. It will be very clear. |author=Marc Guggenheim |author-link=Marc Guggenheim |date=November 23, 2019 |access-date=November 27, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Arrowverse tie-ins ===\nIn December 2018, during the end of the annual crossover \"[[Elseworlds (Arrowverse)|Elseworlds]]\", a follow up crossover was announced titled \"[[Crisis on Infinite Earths (Arrowverse)|Crisis on Infinite Earths]]\" based on the [[Crisis on Infinite Earths|comic book series of the same name]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.denofgeek.com/us/tv/dc-entertainment/278125/crisis-on-infinite-earths-confirmed-as-2019-arrowverse-crossover |title=Crisis on Infinite Earths Confirmed as 2019 Arrowverse Crossover |last=Cecchini |first=Mike |date=December 12, 2018 |website=[[Den of Geek]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190413151225/https://www.denofgeek.com/us/tv/dc-entertainment/278125/crisis-on-infinite-earths-confirmed-as-2019-arrowverse-crossover |archive-date=April 13, 2019 |access-date=May 17, 2019}}</ref> The crossover will feature [[Tyler Hoechlin]] reprising his role as [[Clark Kent (Arrowverse)|Clark Kent / Superman]] from ''[[Supergirl (TV series)|Supergirl]]'', while Routh will portray another version of Superman.<ref name=\"Superman\" /> It took place over five episodes\u2013three in December 2019 and two in January 2020, with ''Legends of Tomorrow''{{'}}s episode of the crossover airing in January.<ref name=\"January 2020\" /><ref name=\"Crisis on Infinite Earths-season5\">{{Cite web |url=https://tvline.com/2019/08/04/arrowverse-crisis-crossover-schedule-black-lightning-cast/ |title=Arrowverse 'Crisis on Infinite Earths' Crossover Adds Black Lightning Stars, Bruce Wayne&nbsp;\u2014 Get Full Schedule |last=Mitovitch |first=Matt Webb |date=August 4, 2019 |website=[[TVLine]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190804214914/https://tvline.com/2019/08/04/arrowverse-crisis-crossover-schedule-black-lightning-cast/ |archive-date=August 4, 2019 |access-date=August 4, 2019}}</ref> The ''Legends of Tomorrow'' episode is considered a special episode, and not the series' season premiere.<ref name=\"Crisis on Infinite Earths-season5\" />\n\n== Marketing ==\nThe first official trailer for the season was released on December 5, 2019.<ref name=\"Season5Trailer\">{{Cite web |url=https://collider.com/dc-legends-of-tomorrow-trailer-season-5/ |title=\u2018DC\u2019s Legends of Tomorrow\u2019 Season 5 Trailer Promises Big Fights and Big Laughs |last=Michael |first=Brendan |date=December 5, 2019 |website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]] |access-date=December 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206004216/https://collider.com/dc-legends-of-tomorrow-trailer-season-5/ |archive-date=December 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<!-- == Release == -->\n== Broadcast ==\nThe season premiered on The CW on January 21, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://ew.com/tv/2019/05/16/cw-fall-2019-schedule-batwoman-nancy-drew/ |title=The CW's 2019 fall schedule revealed: 'Batwoman' and 'Supergirl' team up on Sunday |last=Agard |first=Chancellor |date=May 16, 2019 |website=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190517071156/https://ew.com/tv/2019/05/16/cw-fall-2019-schedule-batwoman-nancy-drew/ |archive-date=May 17, 2019 |access-date=May 17, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"January 2020\" /><ref name=\"CWMidseason2020\">{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/11/the-cw-midseason-premiere-dates-katy-keene-return-dcs-legends-roswell-new-mexico-supernatural-moves-to-monday-1202781471/ |title=The CW Sets Midseason Premiere Dates: 'Katy Keene', Return Of 'DC's Legends', 'Roswell, New Mexico', 'Supernatural' Moves To Monday |last=Petski |first=Denise |date=November 8, 2019 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |url-status=live |access-date=November 8, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191109083953/https://deadline.com/2019/11/the-cw-midseason-premiere-dates-katy-keene-return-dcs-legends-roswell-new-mexico-supernatural-moves-to-monday-1202781471/ |archive-date=November 9, 2019 }}</ref> It is set to run for 15 episodes,<ref>{{Cite AV media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vVyCUe9cOyo |title=Brandon Routh Talks Reprising Superman Role for Arrowverse Crossover |date=July 19, 2019 |last=ExtraTV |time=9:10 |access-date=October 26, 2019 |work=YouTube |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191105083042/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vVyCUe9cOyo&gl=US&hl=en |archive-date=November 5, 2019 }}</ref><ref name=\"FinaleScript\" /> which includes the special episode produced for the \"[[Crisis on Infinite Earths (Arrowverse)|Crisis on Infinite Earths]]\" crossover before the season premiere.<ref name=\"Crisis on Infinite Earths-season5\" />\n<!-- === Home media === -->\n== Reception ==\n\n=== Ratings ===\n{{Television episode ratings\n| width = 99\n\n| n0       = \u2013\n| title0   = [[#ep68|Crisis on Infinite Earths: Part Five]]\n| date0    = January 14, 2020\n| rs0      = 0.5/3\n| viewers0 = 1.35<ref name=\"Special\" />\n| dvr0     = 0.4\n| dvrv0    = 1.03\n| total0   = 0.9\n| totalv0  = 2.38<ref>{{cite web|url=https://programminginsider.com/live7-weekly-ratings-sixteen-broadcast-network-dramas-lead-in-raw-gains-among-total-viewers-topped-by-the-good-doctor/|title=Live+7 Weekly Ratings: Sixteen Broadcast Network Dramas Lead in Raw Gains Among Total Viewers, Topped by 'The Good Doctor'|last=Pucci|first=Douglas|date=January 29, 2020|work=Programming Insider|accessdate=January 29, 2020}}</ref>\n\n| title1    = [[#ep69|Meet the Legends]]\n| date1     = January 21, 2020\n| rs1       = 0.2/1\n| viewers1  = 0.72<ref name=\"5.01\" />\n| dvr1      = 0.3\n| dvrv1     = 0.66\n| total1    = 0.5\n| totalv1   = 1.37<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://programminginsider.com/tuesday-final-ratings-first-day-of-trump-impeachment-trial-draws-more-than-11-million-viewers-across-six-networks/|title=Tuesday Final Ratings: First Day of Trump Impeachment Trial Draws More Than 11 Million Viewers Across Six Network|last=Pucci |first=Douglas |date=February 12, 2020 |website=Programming Insider |access-date=February 12, 2020}}</ref>\n\n| title2    = [[#ep70|Miss Me, Kiss Me, Love Me]]\n| date2     = February 4, 2020\n| rs2       = 0.2\n| viewers2  = 0.79<ref name=\"5.02\"/>\n| dvr2      = 0.2