egends of Tomorrow season 5.jpg\n| caption              = Promotional poster\n| starring             = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Brandon Routh]]\n* [[Caity Lotz]]\n* [[Maisie Richardson-Sellers]]\n* [[Tala Ashe]]\n* [[Jes Macallan]]\n* [[Courtney Ford]]\n* Olivia Swann\n* [[Amy Pemberton|Amy Louise Pemberton]]\n* [[Nick Zano]]\n* [[Dominic Purcell]]\n* [[Matt Ryan (actor)|Matt Ryan]]\n}}\n| country              = United States\n| network              = [[The CW]]\n| first_aired          = {{Start date|2020|1|21}}\n| last_aired           = {{End date|present}}\n| num_episodes         = 7<!--Only increment as a new episode premieres, per the documentation of the template!-->\n| episode_list         = List of Legends of Tomorrow episodes\n}}\nThe fifth season of the American television series ''[[Legends of Tomorrow]]'', which is based on characters from [[DC Comics]], premiered on [[The CW]] on January 21, 2020. The season will consist of 15 episodes, which includes the special episode produced for the \"[[Crisis on Infinite Earths (Arrowverse)|Crisis on Infinite Earths]]\" crossover before the season premiere. It is set in the [[Arrowverse]], sharing continuity with the other television series of the universe, and is a spin-off of ''[[Arrow (TV series)|Arrow]]'' and ''[[The Flash (2014 TV series)|The Flash]]''. The season was produced by [[Greg Berlanti|Berlanti Productions]], [[Warner Bros. Television]], and [[DC Entertainment]], with [[Phil Klemmer]] and [[Keto Shimizu]] serving as [[showrunner]]s.\n\nThe season was ordered in January 2019. Production began that July, and [[Wrap (filmmaking)|wrapped]] in January 2020. Principal cast members [[Brandon Routh]], [[Caity Lotz]], [[Maisie Richardson-Sellers]], [[Tala Ashe]], [[Jes Macallan]], [[Courtney Ford]], [[Amy Pemberton|Amy Louise Pemberton]], [[Nick Zano]], [[Dominic Purcell]] and [[Matt Ryan (actor)|Matt Ryan]] return from previous seasons, while Olivia Swann was promoted to the principal cast from her guest status in season four.\n\n== Episodes ==\n{{See also|List of Legends of Tomorrow episodes}}\n<onlyinclude>{{Episode table |background=#CF905C |overall=5 |season=5 |title=21 |director=12 |writer=31 |airdate=11 |prodcode=6 |viewers=9 |country=U.S. |airdateR=<ref name=\"Futon5\">{{cite web |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/dcs-legends-of-tomorrow/listings/ |title=Shows A-Z - dcs legends of tomorrow on cw |website=[[The Futon Critic]] |accessdate=March 5, 2020}}</ref> |episodes=\n{{Episode table/part|c=#CF905C|p=Special|nopart=y}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Legends of Tomorrow (season 5)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 68\n |EpisodeNumber2  = \u2013\n |Title           = [[Crisis on Infinite Earths (Arrowverse)|Crisis on Infinite Earths: Part Five]]\n |DirectedBy      = [[Gregory Smith (actor)|Gregory Smith]]\n |WrittenBy       = [[Keto Shimizu]] & Ubah Mohamed\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|1|14}}\n |ProdCode        = T13.21908\n |Viewers         = 1.35<ref name=\"Special\">{{Cite web |url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/tuesday-final-ratings-jan-14-2020/ |title='This is Us' adjusts up: Tuesday final ratings |last=Welch |first=Alex |date=January 15, 2020 |website=[[TV by the Numbers]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200117191040/https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/tuesday-final-ratings-jan-14-2020/ |archive-date=January 17, 2020 |access-date=January 15, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Waking up in the newly recreated universe, the Paragons discover they are the only ones who remember the Crisis and that [[Earth-38 (Arrowverse)|Earth-38]] and [[Jefferson Pierce (Arrowverse)|Jefferson Pierce's]] Earth were merged with [[Earth-1 (Arrowverse)|Earth-1]] into a composite universe, later designated as [[Earth-Prime (Arrowverse)|Earth-Prime]]. Not only that, [[Oliver Queen (Arrowverse)|Oliver Queen]]'s second sacrifice gave them all fresh starts. While [[J'onn J'onzz (Arrowverse)|J'onn J'onzz]] uses his psionic powers to bring their allies up to speed, [[Sara Lance]] attempts to find Oliver without success. Later that night, the Paragons are attacked by shadow demons. A restored and remorseful [[Nash Wells]] discovers that the [[Anti-Monitor (Arrowverse)|Anti-Monitor]] is still alive and plotting to renew his destruction of the multiverse. To stop him once and for all, Nash, [[Ray Palmer (Arrowverse)|Ray Palmer]], [[Barry Allen (Arrowverse)|Barry Allen]], and [[Ryan Choi (Arrowverse)|Ryan Choi]] work to develop a bomb to shrink the Anti-Monitor for eternity while the other heroes distract him. Once it is finished, [[Kara Danvers (Arrowverse)|Kara Danvers]] uses it on the Anti-Monitor and sends him to the microverse. Sometime later, Barry, Kara, Sara, J'onn, Jefferson, [[Kate Kane (Arrowverse)|Kate Kane]], and [[Clark Kent (Arrowverse)|Clark Kent]] hold a memorial service for Oliver before agreeing to work together to protect their new world in his memory.\n----\n{{Television crossover note|parts=5|[[Supergirl (season 5)#ep96|''Supergirl'' season 5 episode 9]]|[[Batwoman (TV series)#ep9|''Batwoman'' season 1 episode 9]]|[[The Flash (season 6)#ep123|''The Flash'' season 6 episode 9]]|[[Arrow (season 8)#ep168|''Arrow'' season 8 episode 8]]|-}}\n |LineColor       = CF905C\n}}\n{{Episode table/part|c=#CF905C|p=Season|nopart=y}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Legends of Tomorrow (season 5)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 69\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n |Title           = Meet the Legends\n |DirectedBy      = [[Kevin Mock]]\n |WrittenBy       = [[Grainne Godfree]] & James Eagan\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|1|21}}\n |ProdCode        = T13.21901\n |Viewers         = 0.72<ref name=\"5.01\">{{Cite web |url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/tuesday-final-ratings-jan-21-2020/ |title='NCIS,' 'The Conners,' all others hold: Tuesday final ratings |last=Welch |first=Alex |date=January 23, 2020 |website=TV by the Numbers |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200124015804/https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/tuesday-final-ratings-jan-21-2020/ |archive-date=January 24, 2020 |access-date=January 23, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Following the events of Hey World and [[Neron (Arrowverse)|Neron]]'s defeat, the Legends have become public heroes. With the Time Bureau dismantled, [[Ava Sharpe]] joins the Legends and allows a documentary crew to film them so they can raise funds. Sara, Ray, and [[Mick Rory (Arrowverse)|Mick Rory]] return from the Crisis, but Sara has yet to come to terms with Oliver's death{{efn|name=\"Crisis\"|As depicted in ''[[Crisis on Infinite Earths]]''.}}. Suddenly, a timequake takes place, leading the Legends to 1917 Russia, where [[Grigori Rasputin]] has returned from the dead. The Legends fail to convince Rasputin to kill his killer, so they return to the ''Waverider'', but leave a crew member behind. As a result, the Legends form a plan to stop Rasputin and rescue the crew member before returning to 2020. They then release the documentary to the world, before claiming the film was faked. Meanwhile, in 2020, [[John Constantine (Arrowverse)|John Constantine]] and [[Gary Green (Arrowverse)|Gary Green]] investigate a demon named Masher, who possessed a child in Star City. Constantine performs an exorcism, freeing the child and sending Masher back to Hell. Constantine also returns to Hell, Mick quits writing and passes on his career to [[Mona Wu]], and Nate sees an old message from [[Zari Tomaz|Zari]], asking him to find her in the new timeline.\n |LineColor       = CF905C\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Legends of Tomorrow (season 5)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 70\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n |Title           = Miss Me, Kiss Me, Love Me\n |DirectedBy      = [[David Geddes (cinematographer)|David Geddes]]\n |WrittenBy       = Ray Utarnachitt\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|4}}\n |ProdCode        = T13.21902\n |Viewers         = 0.77<ref name=\"5.02\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-2-4-2020.html |title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 2.4.2020 |last=Metcalf |first=Mitch |date=February 5, 2020 |website=Showbuzz Daily |access-date=February 6, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = The Legends head to 1947, where mobster [[Bugsy Siegel]] has been revived, with Mona coining the term \"Encore\" for these revived individuals. With his new lease on life, Bugsy plans to make it to the top in the world of crime by becoming an information broker. He also gets revenge on his killer, using a gun loaded with hellfire bullets to destroy their body and soul. Meanwhile, Constantine poses as a detective to deal with Bugsy's ex-girlfriend, who's after a bag of money the thug buried. Despite causing chaos, the Legends capture Bugsy, whom Constantine uses to return to hell and kill him with his own Hell Gun before warning Astra to stop.\n |LineColor       = CF905C\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Legends of Tomorrow (season 5)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 71\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n |Title           = Slay Anything\n |DirectedBy      = Alexandra La Roche\n |WrittenBy       = Matthew Maala & Tyron B. Carter\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|11}}\n |ProdCode        = T13.21903\n |Viewers         = 0.74<ref name=\"5.03\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-2-11-2020.html |title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 2.11.2020 |last=Metcalf |first=Mitch |date=February 12, 2020 |website=Showbuzz Daily |access-date=February 12, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Ray believes the Encores can be stopped by reforming them in the past. The Legends test this idea when serial killer Freddy Meyers is encored in 2004 and attacks his high school reunion. Sara, Ava, and Mick head there to stop him while Ray, Nate, and Behrad take [[Nora Darhk]] to 1989 to become Freddy's fairy godmother and fix his prom night. The Legends find evidence of a prank that Freddy's date, Tiffany, and a jock were going to pull, but the former has a change of heart and gets the latter to confess. With Nora's encouragement, Freddy uses his last wish to perform a dance number to show his \"true self\". Zari has flashes of her other life and escapes the ''Waverider'' just as the real killer attacks the prom. To Freddy's horror, the killer is his overly-possessive mother Kathy, whose crime he took the fall for. Behrad manages to knock her out, undoing her damage in 2004. The Legends reconvene at the reunion, learning Freddy and Tiffany got married while Mick reconnects with an old girlfriend, Ali. Meanwhile, Constantine resorts to desperate measures to stop Astra's Encores by facing her mother's ghost, much to Charlie and Gary's dismay.\n |LineColor       = CF905C\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Legends of Tomorrow (season 5)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 72\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n |Title           = A Head of Her Time\n |DirectedBy      = Avi Youabian\n |WrittenBy       = Morgan Faust\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|18}}\n |ProdCode        = T13.21904\n |Viewers         = 0.72<ref name=\"5.04\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-2-18-2020.html |title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 2.18.2020 |last=Metcalf |first=Mitch |date=February 20, 2020 |website=Showbuzz Daily |access-date=February 20, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Sara leaves Ava in charge of the Legends while she heads to Star City for business. An Encore pops up in 1793 France, causing a massacre. The Legends investigate, finding [[Marie Antoinette]], who was encored after her execution. Discovering Marie has magic perfume, the Legends capture her, separating her head from her body. Not understanding how dangerous the perfume is, Zari steals it when Behrad takes her back to 2040 for her own perfume's launch. Behrad, Nate, and Ava go to stop her while Marie's body gets free and steals Mick's Heat Gun. Zari is pushed into a fountain to wash off the perfume and escorted back to the ''Waverider'' before she can damage history any further. They return just as Mick and Ray pin down Marie's body and lock it in [[Martin Stein (Arrowverse)|Martin Stein]]'s old lab, but Astra recalls her back to Hell. Meanwhile, Constantine is tormented by a ghost that was part of his Earth-Prime counterpart's Newcastle crew when she was alive. She reveals that the Loom of Fate is the key and Charlie knows where it is. Charlie reveals she destroyed it, just as Constantine starts coughing up blood.\n|LineColor       = CF905C\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Legends of Tomorrow (season 5)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 73\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n |Title           = Mortal Khanbat\n |DirectedBy      = [[Caity Lotz]]\n |WrittenBy       = Grainne Godfree & Mark Bruner\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|25}}\n |ProdCode        = T13.21905\n |Viewers         = 0.74<ref name=\"5.05\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-2-25-2020.html |title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 2.25.2020 |last=Metcalf |first=Mitch |date=February 26, 2020 |website=Showbuzz Daily |access-date=February 26, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = When he is diagnosed with stage 4 lung cancer, Constantine concludes Astra tampered with his soul coin and forces Ray and Gary to help him find a way to extend his life, but to no avail. Poisoning himself, Constantine goes to Hell and tells Astra that he promised her mother that he would use the Loom of Fate to save them, so she gives him his remaining years back. Meanwhile, the Legends head to 1990s Hong Kong, where [[Genghis Khan]] is attempting to start a new empire by using a hell sword and the contemporary Triads to force [[Charles, Prince of Wales|Prince Charles]] to hand over control of the city to him. Using her powers to disguise herself as Prince Charles, Charlie manages to steal Khan's sword and kill him with it. Following this, Charlie reveals to her friends that she is actually [[Clotho]] of the [[Moirai|Fates]] and that she scattered the Loom of Fate across the multiverse to give everyone free will. Due to the Crisis however, the pieces are now on Earth-Prime and her sisters are out for revenge against her.\n |LineColor       = CF905C\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Legends of Tomorrow (season 5)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 74\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n |Title           = Mr. Parker's Cul-De-Sac\n |DirectedBy      = Ben Hernandez Bray\n |WrittenBy       = Keto Shimizu & James Eagan\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|10}}\n |ProdCode        = T13.21906\n |Viewers         = 0.73<ref name=\"5.06\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-10-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 3.10.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=March 11, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Ray plans a romantic dinner for Nora at Constantine's place, planning to propose to her while Nate and Behrad babysit her latest charge, Pippa, on the ''Waverider''. Unfortunately, her father [[Damien Darhk (Arrowverse)|Damien Darhk]] is \"encored\" following [[Mallus (Legends of Tomorrow)|Mallus]]' demise and steals past Gary's time courier to get to 2020. When Constantine blunders in, Nora tries to pass him off as her lover and her friends as her minions. The ruse fails, forcing Nora to reveal the truth, disappointing Damien. After Pippa wishes everyone into the TV show, ''Mr Parker's Cul-De-Sac'', Nora tells Damien that being a fairy godmother helps her with the trauma of being raised by Mallus' cult instead of him. Damien gives his blessing and everyone is released. Ray and Nora have a makeshift wedding, with Damien advising his new son-in-law that Nora cannot live her life to the fullest as a Legend. He discreetly leaves and kills himself with Khan's blade. Meanwhile, Mick learns someone has libeled his books. With Zari's help, he tracks down a girl named Lita, whom he learns is his and Ali's daughter. Not wishing to taint Lita's life with his presence, Mick erases the visit from everyone's minds.\n |LineColor       = CF905C\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Legends of Tomorrow (season 5)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 75\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 7\n |Title           = Romeo v Juliet: Dawn of Justness\n |DirectedBy      = Alexandra La Roche\n |WrittenBy       = Ray Utarnachitt & Matthew Maala\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|17}}\n |ProdCode        = T13.21907\n |Viewers         = 0.67<ref name=\"5.07\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-17-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 3.17.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=March 18, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = While in 16th century England to retrieve the first piece of the Loom of Fate, the Legends inadvertently inspire [[William Shakespeare]] to rewrite ''[[Romeo and Juliet]]'' as a superhero story just as he was about to write its ending. Even worse, they fail to wipe his mind correctly following a bar fight. Initially, they decide to let the playwright be as they got what they came for. However, Sara refuses to accept this and forces her team to return and convince Shakespeare to write ''Romeo and Juliet'' as intended. After his boss withdraws his actors before a performance, Shakespeare becomes despondent until the Legends offer to fill in for them. Following this, Ray and Nora leave the Legends to live their lives together. Meanwhile, Astra attains a special viewing device to spy on Constantine. However, he catches on quickly and uses a spell to knock her out. When she comes to, she realizes what Constantine is really searching for.\n |LineColor       = CF905C\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Legends of Tomorrow (season 5)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 76\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 8\n |Title           = Zari, Not Zari\n |RTitle          = <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/listings/20200409cw07/|title=(#509) \"Zari, Not Zari\"|website=The Futon Critic |access-date=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n |DirectedBy      = Kevin Mock\n |WrittenBy       = Morgan Faust & Tyron Carter\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|21}}\n |ProdCode        = T13.21909<ref>{{Cite tweet |number=1187442474815328256 |user=ketomizu |title=#LegendsOfTomorrow episode 509 is now in production! Written by @morganfaust and @tyronsaidso and directed by @kevmock |author-link=Keto Shimizu |date=October 24, 2019 |last=Shimizu |first=Keto}}</ref>\n |Viewers         =\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = CF905C\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Legends of Tomorrow (season 5)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 77\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 9\n |Title           = The Great British Fake Off\n |RTitle          = <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/listings/20200312cw06/|title=(#510) \"The Great British Fake Off\"|website=The Futon Critic |access-date=March 12, 2020}}</ref>\n |DirectedBy      = David Geddes\n |WrittenBy       = Jackie Canino\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|28}}<ref>http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/dcs-legends-of-tomorrow/listings/</ref>\n |ProdCode        = T13.21910<ref>{{Cite tweet |number=1192262676463751168 |user=ketomizu |title=#LegendsOfTomorrow episode 510 is now in production! Written by our script coordinator @jackiepcanino and directed by @da_geddes |author-link=Keto Shimizu |date=November 7, 2019 |last=Shimizu |first=Keto}}</ref>\n |Viewers         =\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = CF905C\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Legends of Tomorrow (season 5)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 78\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 10\n |Ti