flagicon|Romania}} [[Talida Tolnai]]\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} Daniela Morari\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} Tereza Ludmila P\u00eeslaru\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} Raluca Iuliana Agrigoroaie\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} [[Ramona Maier|Ramona Farc\u0103u]]\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} Roxana Han (Gatzel)\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} Alina \u021aurca\u0219-Jula\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} Mihaela P\u00e2r\u00e2ianu\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} Mihaela Cr\u0103can\u0103\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} Carmen Buceschi\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} Sanda Criste\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} Alina \u0218orodoc (M\u0103ierean)\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} [[Simona Spiridon]]\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} [[Stelu\u021ba Luca]]\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} Marinela P\u0103tru\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} Artemizia-Aurica Sagmar\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} Olimpia Vere\u0219\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} L\u0103cr\u0103mioara Fiastru\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} Lucia Butn\u0103ra\u0219u\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} Ana \u0218uhai\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} Maria Elena R\u0103doi\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} [[Claudia Constantinescu]]\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} [[Roxana Sz\u00f6l\u00f6si]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n== Coaches ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=left\n|+\n!Period||Coach\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|1978 - 2006||{{flagicon|Rom\u00e2nia}} [[Gheorghe Tadici]]\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|2006 - 2007||{{flagicon|Rom\u00e2nia}} Ioan Gerhardt\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|2007 - 2011||{{flagicon|Rom\u00e2nia}} Sorin R\u0103dulescu\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|2008 - ||{{flagicon|Rom\u00e2nia}} [[Gheorghe Tadici]]\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links== \n* {{Official website|http://www.hczalau.ro/}} \n*{{Facebook|HCZalau}}\n\n{{Liga Na\u021bional\u0103 (women's handball)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zalau}}\n[[Category:Liga Na\u021bional\u0103 (women's handball) clubs]]\n[[Category:Handball clubs established in 1978]]\n[[Category:1978 establishments in Romania]]\n[[Category:Zal\u0103u]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox handball club|\n| image       = HC Zalau.jpg\n| club name   = HC Zal\u0103u\n| full name   = Handball Club Zal\u0103u\n| short name  = Zal\u0103u\n| former names= Silcotub, Silcotex, Textila, Didactica Zal\u0103u \n| founded     = {{Start date and years ago|df=yes|1978}}\n| coulors     = {{colorbox|red}}{{colorbox|blue}}\n| ground      = Sala Sporturilor \"Gheorghe Tadici\"\n| capacity    =   \n| chairman    = {{flagicon|ROU}} Radu Istrate\n| manager     = {{flagicon|ROU}} [[Gheorghe Tadici]]\n| league      = [[Liga Na\u021bional\u0103 (women's handball)|Liga Na\u0163ional\u0103]]\n| season      = [[2018\u201319 Liga Na\u021bional\u0103 (women's handball)|2018\u201319]]\n| position    = Liga Na\u021bional\u0103, 8th of 14\n| website     = http://www.hczalau.ro/\n| colour1     = dodgerblue\n| colour2     = black\n\n| pattern_la1 = _whiteshoulders\n| pattern_b1  = \n| pattern_ra1 = _whiteshoulders\n| pattern_sh1 = _whitesides\n| leftarm1    = 1E90FF\n| body1       = 1E90FF\n| rightarm1   = 1E90FF\n| shorts1     = 000000\n                       \n| pattern_la2 = _whiteshoulders\n| pattern_b2  = \n| pattern_ra2 = _whiteshoulders\n| pattern_sh2 = _whitesides\n| leftarm2    = 800080\n| body2       = 800080\n| rightarm2   = 800080\n| shorts2     = 000000\n}}\n\n'''HC Zal\u0103u''' is a [[team handball|women's handball]] club from [[Zal\u0103u]], [[Romania]], that plays in the [[Liga Na\u0163ional\u0103 (Handbal Feminin)|Romanian Women's Handball League]].\n\nOn domestic level HC Zalau won three league titles (2001,2004,2005) and Romanian Cup once in 2003.\n\nIn Europe HC Zalau won the Women's [[Women's EHF Challenge Cup]] 1995-1996 season and in the same season by participating in the [[EHF Women's Champions Trophy]] won 3rd place. In the 2011-2012 season in the EHF Cup HC Zalau played second final in history, lost against the Russian team Lada Togliatti.\n\n== History <ref>[http://www.magazinsalajean.ro/sport/handbalul-de-performanta-de-30-de-ani-in-salaj Handball performance over 30 years in S\u0103laj]</ref>==\nIn 1978 [[Gheorghe Tadici]] - John Bal Cri\u0219an - Simon Talos trio, with [[Gheorghe Tadici|Tadici]] in the main role, set foot in the city of Mese\u015f a women handball team called Didactica Zal\u0103u.\n\nIn 1979 Didactica Zal\u0103u get to promote Division B, moving, for the first time in official competition at the senior level. In 1980, Didactica Zal\u0103u turns to Textila Zalau,  textile enterprise is willing to invest in handball team.\nFour years later, in 1984 Textila managed to promote the first scene of Romanian handball. Two years later the team would relegate in Division B in the 1985-1986 season and a year later to promote back to the first division after a perfect season. Since then handball team HC Zal\u0103u evolving  Romanian Handball League.\n\nAfter two bronze medals in the seasons 1989 - 1990 and 1990 - 1991, Textila Zal\u0103u turns to Silcotex in 1992. Under this name, he became vice season 1993 - 1994 and in the same year (1994) changed their name for the third time, becoming Silcotub Zal\u0103u.\n\nAgain finishing 2nd in Romanian Handball League in the season 1995 - 1996, Silcotub Zal\u0103u have win at the end of the same season and [[Women's EHF Challenge Cup|EHF Challenge Cup]] or City Cup. Also in 1996 he finished third in the [[EHF Women's Champions Trophy|EHF Champions Trophy]]. For 14 consecutive years from 1994 to 2007 HC Zal\u0103u participated in European Cups, [[EHF Women's Champions League|EHF Champions League]], [[EHF Women's Champions Trophy|EHF Champions Trophy]], [[Women's EHF Cup Winners' Cup|EHF Cup Winners' Cup]], [[Women's EHF Cup|EHF Cup]] and [[Women's EHF Challenge Cup|EHF Challenge Cup]].\n\nAfter the third title in history (2005) team changes its name to HC Zal\u0103u, earning the title of national runner at the end of the 2005-2006 season. At the end of the same season, [[Gheorghe Tadici]] had to leave for the [[CS Oltchim R\u00e2mnicu V\u00e2lcea|Chimistul R\u00e2mnicu V\u00e2lcea]] champion. Separation of Zal\u0103u handball would be almost fatal to the season 2007 - 2008, when HC Zal\u0103u, under the command of John Gherhardt, came to tour the dam to maintain in the National League.\n\nBack to HC Zal\u0103u, after two years of absence, [[Gheorghe Tadici]] again resumed reconstruction of the team, saying it could even be the last in his career coach.\n\n== Arena ==\n*'''Name:''' Sala Sporturilor \u201eGheorghe Tadici\u201d<ref>[http://www.zalausj.ro/cms/hotarari_more.php?id=A5496_0_7_0_M Sports Hall from Zal\u0103u will have the name of coach Gheorghe Tadici]</ref>\n*'''City:''' [[Zal\u0103u]], [[Rom\u00e2nia]] \n*'''Address:''' Mihai Viteazul nr. 77, Zal\u0103u\n\n== Team ==\n===Current squad===\n\n''Squad for the 2019-20 season''\n{{col-begin|width=75%}}\n{{col-2}}\n;Goalkeepers\n\n* {{0}}1 {{flagicon|ROU}} [[Raluca Kelemen]]\n* 16 {{flagicon|ROM}} Adina Sab\u0103u\n* 12 {{flagicon|ROU}} Sara Abed Kader\n;Wingers\n;LW\n\n* {{0}}3 {{flagicon|ROU}} Diana Nichitean\n* 15 {{flagicon|ROU}} Andreea Mihart\n;RW\n* {{0}}8 {{flagicon|ROM}} Cristiana Nica\n* 10 {{flagicon|ROU}} Gabriela Vrabie \n;Line players\n* 14 {{flagicon|ROM}} [[Dana Abed Kader]]\n* 23 {{flagicon|ROU}} Teodora Popescu\n{{col-2}}\n\n;Back players\n* 20 {{flagicon|ROU}} [[Andreea Tecar]]\n* 11 {{flagicon|ROU}} Irina Ivan \n* {{0}}9 {{flagicon|ROU}} Amalia Coman \n* 18 {{flagicon|ROU}} Larisa \u015eerban\n* {{0}}5 {{flagicon|ROU}} Alexandra Severin\n* {{0}}6 {{flagicon|ROU}} Bianca Berbece\n* 22 {{flagicon|ROM}} Sabrina Lazea\n* 19 {{flagicon|ROU}} Alexandra Pricop\n{{Col-end}}\n\n===Transfers===\n:''Transfers for the 2019-2020\n{{Col-begin}}\n{{Col-2}}\n;Joining\n* {{flagicon|ROU}} Gabriela Vrabie (RW)\n* {{flagicon|ROU}} Amalia Coman (CB/LB)\n* {{flagicon|ROU}} Irina Ivan (LB)\n* {{flagicon|ROU}} Sara Abed Kader (GK)\n* {{flagicon|ROU}} Larisa \u015eerban (CB)\n{{Col-2}}\n\n;Leaving\n* {{flagicon|ROU}} Paula Vi\u0219an-Teodoresc (GK) - (Pregnancy)\n* {{flagicon|ROM}} Andrada Trif (RW) - (Pregnancy)\n* {{flagicon|ROU}} Valentina Panici (CB) - [[CS M\u0103gura Cisn\u0103die|M\u0103gura Cisn\u0103die]]\n* {{flagicon|ROU}} [[Roxana Sz\u00f6l\u00f6si]] (CB) - [[CS Minaur Baia Mare (women's handball)|CS Minaur Baia Mare]]\n* {{flagicon|ROU}} Raluca Ionela Irimia (LP) \n{{Col-end}}\n\n== Players<ref>[http://www.frh.ro/pdf/loturi_echipe.xlsx Players]</ref>==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=right\n|+\n!Name||Nationality||Contract until||Date of birth and age\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[Dana Abed Kader|Abed Kader Dana]]||align=\"center\"|{{flagicon|Rom\u00e2nia}}||align=\"center\"|14.01.2021||align=\"right\"|{{Birth date and age|1996|6|21}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Bojdan Alexandra Giorgiana||align=\"center\"|{{flagicon|Rom\u00e2nia}}||align=\"center\"|01.07.2021||align=\"right\"|{{Birth date and age|1998|6|6}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Ciolan Ana C\u0103t\u0103lina||align=\"center\"|{{flagicon|Rom\u00e2nia}}||align=\"center\"|01.06.2018||align=\"right\"|{{Birth date and age|1992|9|29}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Constantinescu Maria Claudia||align=\"center\"|{{flagicon|Rom\u00e2nia}}||align=\"center\"|01.06.2018||align=\"right\"|{{Birth date and age|1994|6|18}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Crap Raluca Ionela||align=\"center\"|{{flagicon|Rom\u00e2nia}}||align=\"center\"|01.06.2018||align=\"right\"|{{Birth date and age|1990|2|4}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Dragut Ana Maria||align=\"center\"|{{flagicon|Rom\u00e2nia}}||align=\"center\"|15.06.2018||align=\"right\"|{{Birth date and age|1990|2|24}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Incule\u021b Ana Maria||align=\"center\"|{{flagicon|Rom\u00e2nia}}||align=\"center\"|01.06.2018||align=\"right\"|{{Birth date and age|1994|10|21}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Kelemen Ioana Raluca||align=\"center\"|{{flagicon|Rom\u00e2nia}}||align=\"center\"|01.07.2021||align=\"right\"|{{Birth date and age|1998|6|24}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Lazea Sabrina Giulia||align=\"center\"|{{flagicon|Rom\u00e2nia}}||align=\"center\"|15.01.2021||align=\"right\"|{{Birth date and age|1997|11|1}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Nica Cristiana||align=\"center\"|{{flagicon|Rom\u00e2nia}}